{
  "text": "We defined the monocular estimator as the average of the Zernike components (describing the corneal wavefront aberrations) of OD and the mirrored Zernike components of OS [CITATION_1] (represented by C sym(OS) below). Therefore, for OS, negative even modes and positive odd modes were sign reversed and averaged with the corresponding Zernike modes of OD:",
